Here are the search results for "gogcli github GOG CLI tool." There are actually **two distinct projects** named "gogcli" on GitHub:

---

### 1. **Magnitus-/gogcli** ‚Äî CLI for GOG.com (the gaming platform)
üîó [github.com/Magnitus-/gogcli](https://github.com/Magnitus-/gogcli)

This is a client to interact with the API of GOG.com. This tool focuses on managing your GOG.com game library from the command line:

- The `gogcli storage copy` command doesn't just mindlessly copy files ‚Äî it actually does a diff between the manifests of both storages and copies only what it must.
- It supports both **filesystem** and **S3** storage backends. For example, if you opted for the S3 storage, you can also copy your games to your local drive using `gogcli storage copy`.
- The GOG API doesn't provide checksums for extras, so you may want to use the `--empty-checksum` flag when file name and file size match.

There's also a companion GUI project:

- üîó [github.com/Twombs/GOGcli-GUI](https://github.com/Twombs/GOGcli-GUI) ‚Äî A frontend program for gogcli.exe by Magnitus. It supports features like checksum (MD5) checking, ZIP file checking, multiple manifest retrieval (batch of 20 or less), and full (all) games manifest retrieval.

---

### 2. **steipete/gogcli** ‚Äî CLI for Google Workspace (not GOG.com)
üîó [github.com/steipete/gogcli](https://github.com/steipete/gogcli)

This is a **different tool** ‚Äî despite the similar name, it's for Google services, not GOG.com. It's a fast, script-friendly CLI for Gmail, Calendar, Chat, Classroom, Drive, Docs, Slides, Sheets, Forms, Apps Script, Contacts, Tasks, People, Groups (Workspace), and Keep (Workspace-only). It features JSON-first output, multiple accounts, and least-privilege auth built in.

It can be installed via Homebrew: `brew install steipete/tap/gogcli`

---

If you're looking for the **GOG.com game library management CLI**, the **Magnitus-/gogcli** project at [github.com/Magnitus-/gogcli](https://github.com/Magnitus-/gogcli) is the one you want.
